%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9e7c527a6f66a8c49a6fab10a94681fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: Day1MorningP
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequenceId: albert_day1_morning_pill
  lines:
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Morning, Andy. Welcome to another beautiful day on the SUNSET16. You\u2019ve
      been assigned maintenance on Section C-12 of the ship again for the foreseeable
      future. Wire duty. It\u2019s up your alley as a Technician."
    sendDelay: 0
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Your efficiency ratings have been stellar these past 5 years. DOLOS is
      pleased.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "It\u2019s what I\u2019m here for."
      nextLineIndex: 2
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Exactly. Now, need a refresher on wiring protocols, or are you good on
      that front?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "A refresher wouldn\u2019t hurt."
      nextLineIndex: 3
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "I know what I\u2019m doing. No refreshers needed."
      nextLineIndex: 4
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "It\u2019s the standard grid-based alignment. Connect the correctly coloured
      endpoints without allowing the paths to cross. Watch out for weird edge cases.
      Don\u2019t improvise the wiring."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: Affirmative.
      nextLineIndex: 5
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "You\u2019ve done this a thousand times. Still, check the manual\u2019s
      instructions whenever you need to. It\u2019s always beneficial to keep one\u2019s
      mind sharp, especially when working for the DOLOS Corporation."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 5
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Any other questions before you head out to boiler room 1A? My shift at
      Section M-67 doesn\u2019t begin for another 20."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices:
    - choiceText: "What\u2019s on your plate today? At Section M-67?"
      nextLineIndex: 6
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "It feels like I\u2019ve been doing this forever\u2026"
      nextLineIndex: 7
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "Thinking about it now\u2026 our collars look quite intricate despite
        their simple appearance."
      nextLineIndex: 9
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: I have no more questions. I have tasks to complete.
      nextLineIndex: 11
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 1
    advanceToLine: 11
    repeat: 1
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "The usual. Monitoring the nuclear core output. All graphs and numbers.
      It\u2019s light work, but you need a keen eye. I always preferred the less
      hands-on assignments. Hated getting oil stuck between my fingernails."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 5
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Space has a way of changing your perception of time. But that\u2019s why
      routines always help. Keeps things orderly."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Trust me, it\u2019s better here than anywhere else on the planet."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 5
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Haha, yeah. The Aegis Collar is a precise system. The DOLOS Corporation
      views aesthetics for a device like that as inconsequential for its function.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 10
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Our job is to wear the collar, not to accessorize it.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 5
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: albert_aegis_collar
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Alright, I\u2019ll let you get to it. DOLOS loves a completed log."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: -1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
    glitch: 0
